% =============================================================================
% data/maths/references.bib
% =============================================================================
%
% Canonical BibTeX bibliography for velocity.report.
%
% This is the single authoritative source for all academic references cited
% across the documentation (architecture docs, maths specs, proposals, and
% plans).  For academic publications, citation keys follow the LastnameYYYY
% convention (e.g. Kalman1960, Ester1996).  For multiple papers by the same
% first author in the same year, an alphabetical suffix is appended (e.g.
% BarShalom1988a, BarShalom1988b).
%
% For standards, software, datasets, tooling, and vendor documentation, more
% descriptive mnemonic keys may be used instead (e.g. CityJSON, ROSVelodyne,
% OSMSimple3DBuildings, HesaiPandar40P).
% Sections mirror the reference groupings in
%   docs/lidar/architecture/lidar-data-layer-model.md
%
% BibTeX conventions used throughout:
%   - Proper nouns / initialisms that must not be lowercased by bibliography
%     styles are wrapped in an extra pair of braces, e.g. {{DBSCAN}}.
%   - The ampersand in author names is escaped as {\&} where it appears in
%     titles; the author field uses standard " and " notation.
%   - @inproceedings for conference papers, @article for journals, @book for
%     monographs, @misc / @manual for standards and user manuals.
%
% Last updated: 2026-03-22
% =============================================================================


